The most common compound described here is **dimethylsulfoxonium methylide** (from dimethyl sulfoxide, DMSO, and methyl iodide).

\boxed{\text{DMSO (Dimethyl sulfoxide)}}

This reagent generates the ylide upon treatment with methyl iodide and base, which efficiently cyclopropanates alkenes via a Simmons-Smith-like mechanism.
